How We Share Your Information
We may share your information with third parties
in the following ways::
1.
With Service Providers:
We work with trusted third-party partners who assist us in operating the game and providing services such as analytics, payment processing, customer support, and marketing. These partners may have access to certain types of information (e.g., gameplay data, device information) but only as needed to perform their functions and in compliance with our privacy practices.
2.
Third-Party SDKs:
Our game may include third-party Software Development Kits (SDKs) that help us provide essential features such as analytics, advertising, or social media integration. These SDKs may collect data like your device identifiers, interaction data, or location. Some of the SDKs we use include:
l
Analytics SDKs: Used to track gameplay behavior, session duration, and user engagement.
l
Ad Networks SDKs: For serving personalized ads based on user interests and activity.
3.
Advertising Partners:
We may share information, such as your device ID, game interactions, or geographic location, with our advertising partners to serve relevant ads. These partners may combine this data with other information they have collected about you across their services to deliver more personalized advertising.
4.
Endpoints and Data Types:
We may use secure endpoints to transmit data such as:
l
Player Profiles and Game Progress: Stored on our servers or with cloud providers to synchronize gameplay across devices.
l
In-Game Purchases and Payment Details: Shared with third-party payment processors to facilitate transactions.
l
Crash Reports and Bug Fixes: Sent to our development teams or external analytics providers to improve game stability.
